Populate Staging table using JSON file 12

Load Staging table using JSON file now that we have populated table using the Excel File.

Create a Data Flow Task.


Drag Script Component into the DFT and select the OLE DB Destination for our destination.


Now we will configured our Script Component. Double Click the Script Component Transformation. Select Inputs and Outputs. 

Make sure to add all Output Columns, and choose Unicode String data type along with the length of 255.


Now we will edit the script.

Now we will be inputting a bit of code. Just copy and paste the code below into the relevant sections. 

#region Namespaces

using System;

using System.Data;

using Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Pipeline.Wrapper;

using Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime.Wrapper;

using Healthcare;

using System.IO;

using System.Web.Script.Serialization;

using System.Collections.Generic;

#endregion

Next bit of code:

    public override void CreateNewOutputRows()

    {

        /*

        Add rows by calling the AddRow method on the member variable named "<Output Name>Buffer".

        For example, call MyOutputBuffer.AddRow() if your output was named "MyOutput".

        */

        String jsonFileContent = File.ReadAllText(@"C:\Users\alvin\Documents\Alvin Arunkumar IPBC folder\Data Warehouse\Project 1\Healthcare_Census_Files\CensusFiles_B.json");

        JavaScriptSerializer js = new JavaScriptSerializer() { MaxJsonLength = 86753090 };

        List<Census> ProductListV = js.Deserialize<List<Census>>(jsonFileContent);

        foreach (Census ProductList in ProductListV)

        {

            Output0Buffer.AddRow();

            Output0Buffer.Procedure = ProductList.Procedure;

            Output0Buffer.ProviderId = ProductList.ProviderId;

            Output0Buffer.AsOfDate = ProductList.AsOfDate;

            Output0Buffer.ProviderName = ProductList.ProviderName;

            Output0Buffer.ProviderStreet = ProductList.ProviderStreet;

            Output0Buffer.ProviderCity = ProductList.ProviderCity;

            Output0Buffer.ProviderState = ProductList.ProviderState;

            Output0Buffer.ProviderZip = ProductList.ProviderZip;

            Output0Buffer.HospitalRegion = ProductList.HospitalRegion;

            Output0Buffer.TotalDischarges = ProductList.TotalDischarges;

            Output0Buffer.AvgCoveredCharges = ProductList.AvgCoveredCharges;

            Output0Buffer.AvgTotalPayments = ProductList.AvgTotalPayments;

            Output0Buffer.AvgMedicarePayments = ProductList.AvgMedicarePayments;

            Output0Buffer.State = ProductList.State;

            Output0Buffer.StateFIPS = ProductList.StateFIPS;

            Output0Buffer.InsuredMales1825 = ProductList.InsuredMales1825;

            Output0Buffer.NoninsuredMales1825 = ProductList.NoninsuredMales1825;

            Output0Buffer.Females1825WInsurance = ProductList.Females1825WInsurance;

            Output0Buffer.Females1825NoInsurance = ProductList.Females1825NoInsurance;

            Output0Buffer.AdminFirstName = ProductList.AdminFirstName;

            Output0Buffer.AdminLastName = ProductList.AdminLastName;

            Output0Buffer.AdminPhoneNumber = ProductList.AdminPhoneNumber;

            Output0Buffer.AdminEmail = ProductList.AdminEmail;

            Output0Buffer.AdminStateResidence = ProductList.AdminStateResidence;

            Output0Buffer.ProductType = ProductList.ProductType;

            Output0Buffer.ProprietaryName = ProductList.ProprietaryName;

            Output0Buffer.NonProprietaryName = ProductList.NonProprietaryName;

            Output0Buffer.DosageForm = ProductList.DosageForm;

            Output0Buffer.Route = ProductList.Route;

            Output0Buffer.LabelerName = ProductList.LabelerName;

            Output0Buffer.SubstanceName = ProductList.SubstanceName;

            Output0Buffer.DosageUnit = ProductList.DosageUnit;


        }

    }

}

Copy and paste the above code in this section. Make special note of the highlighted line below. That will have to be your own individual file destination when you down my zipped JSON file.


Next we need to add a Class, name the Class Census when prompted.


The code to populated the Class is below:

using System;

using System.Collections.Generic;

using System.Linq;

using System.Text;

using System.Threading.Tasks;


namespace Healthcare

{

    class Census

    {

        public string Procedure { get; set; }

        public string ProviderId { get; set; }

        public string AsOfDate { get; set; }

        public string ProviderName { get; set; }

        public string ProviderStreet { get; set; }

        public string ProviderCity { get; set; }

        public string ProviderState { get; set; }

        public string ProviderZip { get; set; }

        public string HospitalRegion { get; set; }

        public string TotalDischarges { get; set; }

        public string AvgCoveredCharges { get; set; }

        public string AvgTotalPayments { get; set; }

        public string AvgMedicarePayments { get; set; }

        public string State { get; set; }

        public string StateFIPS { get; set; }

        public string InsuredMales1825 { get; set; }

        public string NoninsuredMales1825 { get; set; }

        public string Females1825WInsurance { get; set; }

        public string Females1825NoInsurance { get; set; }

        public string AdminFirstName { get; set; }

        public string AdminLastName { get; set; }

        public string AdminPhoneNumber { get; set; }

        public string AdminEmail { get; set; }

        public string AdminStateResidence { get; set; }

        public string ProductType { get; set; }

        public string ProprietaryName { get; set; }

        public string NonProprietaryName { get; set; }

        public string DosageForm { get; set; }

        public string Route { get; set; }

        public string LabelerName { get; set; }

        public string SubstanceName { get; set; }

        public string DosageUnit { get; set; }

    }

}


Now the Script Component should be configured. Select the OLE DB Destination and make sure to choose the appropriate connection manager and table and map the proper columns.




Run the package and the files will populate.
